The standards shall include:
The required qualifications for teachers, administrators, and other professionals serving a child with a disability;
Procedures for the identification, evaluation, educational placement, and provision of a free appropriate public education for a child with a disability who requires the provision of special education and related services;
Guidelines for curricula, instructional materials, equipment, and the organization, administration, and supervision of the program, including accounting, auditing, and reporting procedures;
Provisions for local, regional, and State day and residential centers for children with disabilities who cannot be served appropriately in the public schools;
Coordination of these special education services with services given by any other government agency; and
Guidelines for approval of placement in nonpublic schools or facilities if appropriate public services are not available.
